  "body": "Seems ecently (after 1.6.0) we introduced some naming inconsistency in Envoy API for extensions.\r\n\r\nIn API, everything is singular except [`grpc_credentials`](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/tree/master/api/envoy/config/grpc_credentials/), but in `{source,test}/extensions` everything is plural.\r\n\r\nMy suggestion is we can make at least rename `api/config/grpc_credentials` to singular as it is only v2alpha, and then potentially (optionally) rename extensions in `{source,test}/extensions` to singular. It's impossible to make Extensions API plural as packages like `api.config.filter` is frozen.\r\n\r\nThen we should make a note in STYLE.md or REPO_LAYOUT.md.\r\n\r\nThoughts? @mattklein123 ",
